figures.caption: Figure 1: Hypergraph with 7 vertices (axioms) and 4 edges (conflict sets). Both the maximum degree of the hypergraph and the size of the largest edge are 3.

Table 1: Empirical results for the probabilistic query graduatedFrom(Individual, x) (top) and hasAcademicAdvisor(Individual, x) (bottom). The values are averaged over 100 repetitions of the 50 probabilistic queries. ts: seconds to compute samples for one connected component; MRR: mean reciprocal rank measure values; p@1: precision @ 1.
Figure 2: A knowledge base fragment with object A Einstein and its properties. Some of the minimal conflicts between property assertions (edges in the graph) are indicated by hyperedges.
